# Directus Conventions

## Client setup

The Directus client is configured in `src/lib/server/directus.ts`:

- Uses `@directus/sdk` with GraphQL transport
- Authenticated via static token from environment variables
- The `getDirectusData` function accepts a fetch instance and a GraphQL query string

## Environment variables

- `PRIVATE_DIRECTUS_URL` / `DIRECTUS_URL` — Directus instance URL
- `PRIVATE_DIRECTUS_TOKEN` / `DIRECTUS_TOKEN` — static access token

## Query patterns

- GraphQL queries are defined in `src/lib/util/cms/queries.ts`
- Queries are string templates, not typed SDK calls
- This is an extraction candidate — typed query patterns should eventually move to `bravobyte-data-core`

## Extraction notes

The following are candidates for shared extraction:

| Code | Target repo | Timing |
|------|------------|--------|
| Directus client factory | `bravobyte-data-core` | extract later (after boundary settles) |
| GraphQL query helpers | `bravobyte-data-core` | extract later |
| Content type definitions | `bravobyte-types` | extract soon |
| Content mapping utilities | `bravobyte-data-core` | extract later |

## Rules

- Keep Directus-related server code in `src/lib/server/`
- Keep query definitions in `src/lib/util/cms/`
- Do not expose Directus SDK types directly in UI components — use mapped types
- All Directus access must go through server-side code (no client-side CMS calls)
